      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Start Fuel quality management With Real Operating Data"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "high-runtime generator fleets in Brisbane usually perform better when fuel quality management decisions begin with measured load behaviour instead of rough assumptions. Teams should map startup demand, duty cycle, and environmental constraints before they lock scope or commit commercial terms. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "a",
            "url": "https://www.business.qld.gov.au/running-business/protect-business/risk-management/business-continuity-planning",
            "title": null,
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Queensland business continuity planning guidance"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is a useful baseline for defining critical-load priorities and minimum runtime expectations."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Capture startup and steady-state demand as separate values before seeking quotes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Document access, lifting, and delivery constraints that could delay mobilisation."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Confirm switchboard interfaces and temporary distribution responsibilities early."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Align fuel, noise, and site operating windows to realistic project conditions."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This front-end discipline gives operations, procurement, and service teams a shared starting point, reducing rework and improving confidence when conditions change on site."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Match Service Controls To Fuel degradation and supply risk"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Service coverage should reflect fuel degradation and supply risk, not a generic calendar. Brisbane environments often combine variable weather, constrained access, and tight production windows, so response models need clear priorities. Reference material from "
          },
          {
            "type": "a",
            "url": "https://www.worksafe.qld.gov.au/",
            "title": null,
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "WorkSafe Queensland"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " can help teams shape safe inspection routines and escalation practices without creating unnecessary complexity."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Define response tiers for business-hours, after-hours, and incident-critical faults."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Pair inspection intervals with runtime intensity rather than fixed monthly habits."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Track alarm history and recurring symptoms in a single service log."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add weather-aware checks using "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "a",
                    "url": "https://www.bom.gov.au/",
                    "title": null,
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Bureau of Meteorology"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " forecasts during high-risk periods."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A risk-based service pattern reduces avoidable outages and supports better decisions when operations need rapid stabilisation under pressure."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Compare Hire, Service, And Ownership Using A Practical Decision Matrix"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When high-runtime generator fleets teams compare hire, service, and ownership pathways, they should evaluate operational fit as carefully as price. A simple matrix helps stakeholders align technical requirements with commercial outcomes, and "
          },
          {
            "type": "a",
            "url": "https://www.standards.org.au/",
            "title": null,
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Standards Australia"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " can guide discussions about baseline quality and documentation expectations."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "children": [
          {
